</p>
<p>
    Eugene benefits from its location near tributaries like the McKenzie and Willamette rivers. These waterways serve as migratory paths for several salmon species, including chum. Although chum runs are more prevalent in coastal rivers, Eugene offers easy access to those locations with minimal travel. Combine that with the city’s vibrant angling community, available amenities, and fishing culture, and you’ve got a prime base for any salmon angler.
</p>
