<h2>
    Fishing Techniques That Work
</h2>
<h3>
    Spin Casting Tips for Chum Salmon
</h3>
<p>
    Spin casting is a favorite among chum anglers due to its versatility and ease. Use a medium-heavy rod with a spinning reel and 12-15 lb line. Top-performing lures include:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        Pink or chartreuse jigs
    </li>
    <li>
        Blue Fox Vibrax spinners (#3-5)
    </li>
    <li>
        Corky and yarn setups
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Fish slowly and let the lure bounce along the riverbed. Chum tend to strike out of aggression, so keep presentations lively.
</p>
<h3>
    Fly Fishing for Chum Salmon
</h3>
<p>
    Fly fishing for chum salmon is increasingly popular. Use an 8-10 weight rod and sink-tip line. Streamers in pink, purple, or chartreuse are especially effective. Cast quartering downstream and strip the fly aggressively — chum love movement.
</p>
<h3>
    Best Baits and Lures
</h3>
<p>
    Live bait like cured roe is always a strong option when legal. For lures, focus on flashy colors and movement. Chum aren’t particularly subtle, so your tackle shouldn’t be either.
</p>

